properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.config.enabled
properties.description: Enables Spring Cloud GCP Config.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.config.name
properties.description: Name of the application.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.config.profile
properties.description: Comma-delimited string of profiles under which the app is running. Gets its default value from the {@code spring.profiles.active} property, falling back on the {@code spring.profiles.default} property.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.config.project-id
properties.description: Overrides the GCP project ID specified in the Core module.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.config.timeout-millis
properties.description: Timeout for Google Runtime Configuration API calls.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.logging.enabled
properties.description: Auto-configure Google Cloud Stackdriver logging for Spring MVC.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.project-id
properties.description: GCP project ID where services are running.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.emulator-host
properties.description: The host and port of the local running emulator. If provided, this will setup the client to connect against a running pub/sub emulator.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.enabled
properties.description: Auto-configure Google Cloud Pub/Sub components.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.project-id
properties.description: Overrides the GCP project ID specified in the Core module.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.publisher.batching.delay-threshold-seconds
properties.description: The delay threshold to use for batching. After this amount of time has elapsed (counting from the first element added), the elements will be wrapped up in a batch and sent.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.publisher.batching.element-count-threshold
properties.description: The element count threshold to use for batching.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.publisher.batching.enabled
properties.description: Enables batching if true.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.publisher.batching.flow-control.limit-exceeded-behavior
properties.description: The behavior when the specified limits are exceeded.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.publisher.batching.flow-control.max-outstanding-element-count
properties.description: Maximum number of outstanding elements to keep in memory before enforcing flow control.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.publisher.batching.flow-control.max-outstanding-request-bytes
properties.description: Maximum number of outstanding bytes to keep in memory before enforcing flow control.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.publisher.batching.request-byte-threshold
properties.description: The request byte threshold to use for batching.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.publisher.executor-threads
properties.description: Number of threads used by every publisher.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.publisher.retry.initial-retry-delay-seconds
properties.description: InitialRetryDelay controls the delay before the first retry. Subsequent retries will use this value adjusted according to the RetryDelayMultiplier.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.publisher.retry.initial-rpc-timeout-seconds
properties.description: InitialRpcTimeout controls the timeout for the initial RPC. Subsequent calls will use this value adjusted according to the RpcTimeoutMultiplier.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.publisher.retry.jittered
properties.description: Jitter determines if the delay time should be randomized.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.publisher.retry.max-attempts
properties.description: MaxAttempts defines the maximum number of attempts to perform. If this value is greater than 0, and the number of attempts reaches this limit, the logic will give up retrying even if the total retry time is still lower than TotalTimeout.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.publisher.retry.max-retry-delay-seconds
properties.description: MaxRetryDelay puts a limit on the value of the retry delay, so that the RetryDelayMultiplier can't increase the retry delay higher than this amount.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.publisher.retry.max-rpc-timeout-seconds
properties.description: MaxRpcTimeout puts a limit on the value of the RPC timeout, so that the RpcTimeoutMultiplier can't increase the RPC timeout higher than this amount.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.publisher.retry.retry-delay-multiplier
properties.description: RetryDelayMultiplier controls the change in retry delay. The retry delay of the previous call is multiplied by the RetryDelayMultiplier to calculate the retry delay for the next call.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.publisher.retry.rpc-timeout-multiplier
properties.description: RpcTimeoutMultiplier controls the change in RPC timeout. The timeout of the previous call is multiplied by the RpcTimeoutMultiplier to calculate the timeout for the next call.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.publisher.retry.total-timeout-seconds
properties.description: TotalTimeout has ultimate control over how long the logic should keep trying the remote call until it gives up completely. The higher the total timeout, the more retries can be attempted.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.subscriber.executor-threads
properties.description: Number of threads used by every subscriber.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.subscriber.flow-control.limit-exceeded-behavior
properties.description: The behavior when the specified limits are exceeded.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.subscriber.flow-control.max-outstanding-element-count
properties.description: Maximum number of outstanding elements to keep in memory before enforcing flow control.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.subscriber.flow-control.max-outstanding-request-bytes
properties.description: Maximum number of outstanding bytes to keep in memory before enforcing flow control.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.subscriber.max-ack-extension-period
properties.description: The optional max ack extension period in seconds for the subscriber factory.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.subscriber.parallel-pull-count
properties.description: The optional parallel pull count setting for the subscriber factory.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.subscriber.pull-endpoint
properties.description: The optional pull endpoint setting for the subscriber factory.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.subscriber.retry.initial-retry-delay-seconds
properties.description: InitialRetryDelay controls the delay before the first retry. Subsequent retries will use this value adjusted according to the RetryDelayMultiplier.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.subscriber.retry.initial-rpc-timeout-seconds
properties.description: InitialRpcTimeout controls the timeout for the initial RPC. Subsequent calls will use this value adjusted according to the RpcTimeoutMultiplier.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.subscriber.retry.jittered
properties.description: Jitter determines if the delay time should be randomized.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.subscriber.retry.max-attempts
properties.description: MaxAttempts defines the maximum number of attempts to perform. If this value is greater than 0, and the number of attempts reaches this limit, the logic will give up retrying even if the total retry time is still lower than TotalTimeout.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.subscriber.retry.max-retry-delay-seconds
properties.description: MaxRetryDelay puts a limit on the value of the retry delay, so that the RetryDelayMultiplier can't increase the retry delay higher than this amount.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.subscriber.retry.max-rpc-timeout-seconds
properties.description: MaxRpcTimeout puts a limit on the value of the RPC timeout, so that the RpcTimeoutMultiplier can't increase the RPC timeout higher than this amount.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.subscriber.retry.retry-delay-multiplier
properties.description: RetryDelayMultiplier controls the change in retry delay. The retry delay of the previous call is multiplied by the RetryDelayMultiplier to calculate the retry delay for the next call.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.subscriber.retry.rpc-timeout-multiplier
properties.description: RpcTimeoutMultiplier controls the change in RPC timeout. The timeout of the previous call is multiplied by the RpcTimeoutMultiplier to calculate the timeout for the next call.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.pubsub.subscriber.retry.total-timeout-seconds
properties.description: TotalTimeout has ultimate control over how long the logic should keep trying the remote call until it gives up completely. The higher the total timeout, the more retries can be attempted.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.security.iap.algorithm
properties.description: Encryption algorithm used to sign the JWK token.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.security.iap.audience
properties.description: Non-dynamic audience string to validate.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.security.iap.enabled
properties.description: Auto-configure Google Cloud IAP identity extraction components.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.security.iap.header
properties.description: Header from which to extract the JWK key.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.security.iap.issuer
properties.description: JWK issuer to verify.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.security.iap.registry
properties.description: Link to JWK public key registry.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.sql.credentials
properties.description: Overrides the GCP OAuth2 credentials specified in the Core module.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.sql.database-name
properties.description: Name of the database in the Cloud SQL instance.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.sql.enabled
properties.description: Auto-configure Google Cloud SQL support components.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.sql.instance-connection-name
properties.description: Cloud SQL instance connection name. [GCP_PROJECT_ID]:[INSTANCE_REGION]:[INSTANCE_NAME].

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.storage.enabled
properties.description: Auto-configure Google Cloud Storage components.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.trace.authority
properties.description: HTTP/2 authority the channel claims to be connecting to.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.trace.compression
properties.description: Compression to use for the call.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.trace.deadline-ms
properties.description: Call deadline.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.trace.enabled
properties.description: Auto-configure Google Cloud Stackdriver tracing components.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.trace.max-inbound-size
properties.description: Maximum size for an inbound message.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.trace.max-outbound-size
properties.description: Maximum size for an outbound message.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.trace.num-executor-threads
properties.description: Number of threads to be used by the Trace executor.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.trace.project-id
properties.description: Overrides the GCP project ID specified in the Core module.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.trace.wait-for-ready
properties.description: Waits for the channel to be ready in case of a transient failure. Defaults to failing fast in that case.

properties.name: spring.cloud.gcp.vision.enabled
properties.description: Auto-configure Google Cloud Vision components.
